This paper is about abstractive summarization, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. The paper discusses methods for selecting and fusing sentences to create a summary sentence, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions ranking and modeling, which are common themes in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve training and testing models, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
